1932;;The Greeks Had a Word for Them;;American;;Lowell Sherman;;Joan Blondell, Madge Evans;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Greeks_Had_a_Word_for_Them;;Jean, Polaire, and Schatze are ex-showgirls who put their money together in order to rent a luxurious penthouse apartment. They are out to get wealthy boyfriends by dressing and acting like millionaires themselves. Jean shows herself to be determined and ruthless, leaving the other girls behind. The other two are more sensitive and trustworthy but only one woman will be able to find a rich husband. Which is she?